platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/retro/Input.tsx:14-16 uses template literal concatenation: `${base} ${ariaInvalid ? '...' : ''} ${className}`. Replace with cn(). Also explicitly destructure 'aria-invalid' from props (currently accessed as props['aria-invalid'] on line 15 after rest-spreading — fragile pattern). Refactored shape:

const Input = forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, InputProps>(
  ({ type = 'text', placeholder = 'Enter text', className, 'aria-invalid': ariaInvalid, ...props }, ref) => (
    <input
      ref={ref}
      type={type}
      placeholder={placeholder}
      aria-invalid={ariaInvalid}
      className={cn(
        'w-full rounded border-2 px-4 py-2 shadow-md transition focus:shadow-xs focus:outline-hidden',
        ariaInvalid && 'border-destructive text-destructive shadow-destructive shadow-xs',
        className,
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  ),
);

For NumberStepper (platform/browser-extension/src/side-panel/components/retro/NumberStepper.tsx:51), the outer div uses template literal: `border-border inline-flex ... ${className}`. Import cn and switch to cn('border-border inline-flex ...', className).
